positional arguement: this is an arguement that must be place in the same position that the parameter was declared
 and when input in the argument when calling the function will or might misbehave and give a ligical error.

keyword arguement: this here is when the arguement can place anywhere in any position without caring about the placement
eg in the param we 

when making a keyword argument menaing you can declare the params name and scatter the value when calling the function. the positional arguement must come first before the keyword arg
eg function(999, 21, name = "kuye") name = is a keyword arg

abituary arg is when you dont know the number or argument the function caller might input you use an arbituary arg a star before the param declaration
*name
